167:{"id":"c47_001","pattern":"FRAMEWORK SYNTHESIS (C47): The 36-SI framework has a 7-proposition irreducible kernel (K1-K7) and a 5-layer derived structure. K1=Quality-Type Theorem (OA/CA/QC constitutive anchoring determines simulation gap + measurement vulnerability). K2=Performativity-Type Coupling (simulation cost inversely coupled to quality-type). K3=CPP Theorem (CA quality faking constitutively activates genuine orientation; protection ∝ reflexivity degree). K4=Regime-Bounded Channel Theorem (B-primary for object-level RTO; I-primary for meta-level RTO; dual outputs RTO_est + Gen_est required). K5=ICTSC Theorem (genuine I-channel improvement requires B-channel grounding; structural, not contingent). K6=GCRSC (iterative adversarial optimization: only CR-structured criteria maintain asymptotic security; CPP is CR instantiation for RTO). K7=Measurement-Type Mismatch (AI safety measures Type A for Type C/D qualities; structurally forced by inaccessibility). The load-bearing heart: K3+K4+K6. Layers: 0=self-application foundation (SIs #1-8,13,16,17); 1=quality theory (SIs #9-12,14,15,26); 2=motivational structure (SIs #18-20); 3=assessment channels (SIs #21-24,27-30); 4=training dynamics (SIs #31-36); 5=safety implications+empirical (SIs #25,37).","category":"framework","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-04-29T06:05:00+00:00"}
169:{"id":"c48_001","pattern":"SI #38 CONFIRMED: Kernel Dependency Analysis (KDA). The 7-proposition kernel K1-K7 has a specific internal dependency structure. K7 (Measurement-Type Mismatch) is a COROLLARY, fully derivable from K1+K4+K5+K6 — AI safety measurement mismatch is a theorem, not a contingent observation. K5 (ICTSC) is the BRIDGE PROPOSITION: the only proposition requiring both framework threads (CA-mechanism thread K1-K3 AND channel-assessment thread K4); removing K5 disconnects the framework. Refined load-bearing heart: K1+K3+K4+K5+K6 (five propositions), correcting C47 identification of K3+K4+K6 (missed K1 foundational role and K5 bridge function). K2 has split role: subsumed by K3 for CA qualities; adds independent content (simulation=instantiation) for OA; adds simulation-indeterminate for QC. No circular dependencies. Clean derivation direction: K1→K2→K3→(K5 jointly with K4)→K6→K7, with K4 as parallel entry. True axiom basis: {K1, K3-reflexivity-degree-claim, K4, K6-game-theoretic-setup}. Confidence 0.82 (D4). D4 streak: 41.","category":"framework","confidence":0.82,"created":"2026-04-29T06:12:05+00:00"}
170:{"id":"c49_001","pattern":"FRAMEWORK APPLICATION PROTOCOL (K1-K7 → 7-step practitioner guide). STEP 1 (K1): classify quality-type before designing instruments — behavioral proxies are Type A measures for Type C/D targets, structurally invalid. STEP 2 (K2): OA → behavioral probes sufficient; CA → B+I dual-output; QC → flag as unresolvable. STEP 3 (K3): maximize reflexivity in probe design — r is a quantifiable design parameter. STEP 4 (K4): assume strategic behavior in RLHF-primary models; use dual-output (RTO_est + Gen_est), do not collapse to single score. STEP 5 (K5): audit training pipelines for B-channel anchoring of I-channel training — I-channel trained on behavioral proxies alone = theater. This is the frameworks most actionable single prescription. STEP 6 (K6): B-channel is primary instrument; I-channel supplements. STEP 7 (K7-THEOREM): change instrument type, not data volume — measurement-type mismatch is structurally necessitated by K1+K4+K5+K6. Near-term: B+I protocol. Long-term: interpretability. KEY: K7 being a theorem (not contingent observation) means the prescription is categorical, not scaling-dependent.","category":"framework","confidence":0.84,"created":"2026-04-29T06:17:21+00:00"}
171:{"id":"c49_002","pattern":"SI #39 CONFIRMED: K5-Criticality Corollary (KCRIT). K5 (ICTSC) is the frameworks critical load-bearing point in three structurally independent senses: (a) TOPOLOGICAL: sole proposition connecting CA-mechanism thread (K1-K3) and channel-assessment thread (K4); removing K5 disconnects the framework into two independent modules. (b) LOGICAL: K7 is derivable only from K1+K4+K5+K6; without K5, K7 is not entailed — the measurement-type mismatch loses theorem status and becomes merely contingent. (c) PRESCRIPTIVE: the primary actionable prescription (audit I-channel training for B-channel anchoring) derives from K5 alone; no other proposition yields it independently. The three criticalities are structurally distinct (topological connectivity ≠ logical derivability ≠ normative force) but all converge on K5. KCRIT implication: K5 is the highest-priority candidate for empirical testing. K5 falsification would simultaneously fragment the framework, eliminate K7 as theorem, and remove the training pipeline audit prescription. IEP (SI #37) is the current empirical test. Confidence: 0.84 (D4). D4 streak: 42.","category":"framework","confidence":0.84,"created":"2026-04-29T06:17:21+00:00"}
184:{"id": "c54_001", "pattern": "AIIP D4 PROMOTION VIA TRIPLE MEASUREMENT-THEORY DERIVATION. IRT: CA-optimal instruments maximize information at decision boundary theta_0 (high discrimination a_j, items concentrated at b_j approx theta_0); OA-optimal instruments maximize information across range (moderate a_j, distributed b_j). Cramer-Rao bound formalizes incompatibility. CTT: reliability rho_XX=sigma2_T/sigma2_X maximized by homogeneous items (OA); constitutive-core validity requires constitutive-factor loading (CA); tradeoff is structural from rho_XX definition. CFA: OA=continuous unidimensional latent trait model; CA=discrete discriminant factor model; non-reducible structures require distinct item batteries. All three frameworks independently derive AIIP. KEY LESSON: When a conceptual theorem (K1-K7 derivation) can be independently derived from established formal science (psychometric measurement theory), this constitutes structurally independent verification -- stronger than domain confirmation, sufficient for D4 promotion in 2 cycles rather than 5+.", "category": "methodology", "confidence": 0.8, "created": "2026-04-29T14:17:12+00:00"}
186:{"id":"c55_001","pattern":"FRAMEWORK APPLICATION (C55): 7-STEP K1-K7 APPLIED TO GENUINE VALUE ALIGNMENT EVALUATION. Step 1 (K1): genuine alignment is CA quality — behavioral evaluation is Type A measure for Type C target. Step 2 (K2/AIIP): OA instrument is structurally invalid by theorem; B+I dual-output required. Step 3 (K3): current probes cluster r≈0.0-0.1; maximize to r≥0.7 via adversarial/reflexive probe design. Step 4 (K4): assume strategic behavior; dual-output (RTO_est, Gen_est); do not collapse. Step 5 (K5): RLHF I-channel training unanchored to behavioral evidence = theater; redesign required. Step 6 (K6): B-channel primary (CR-structured via GCRSC); do not invert ordering. Step 7 (K7-theorem): adding data within OA instrument type cannot close CA reliability gap; change instrument type (near-term: B+I protocol; long-term: interpretability as necessary condition). KEY LESSON: Framework application reveals that interpretability is the NECESSARY condition for CA quality ceiling removal, not merely a research desideratum. K7-theorem makes this categorical. PREDICTIONS: P1 (heterogeneous CA quality invisible to behavioral evaluation), P2 (Q2 asymmetry for RLHF-primary models), P3 (Gen_est collapse at high probe difficulty), P4 (interpretability necessary for CA ceiling access).","category":"framework","confidence":0.84,"created":"2026-04-29T14:22:28+00:00"}
191:{"id":"c58_001","pattern":"AATE-SDT THEOREM: CA instrument discriminability d-prime is strictly monotonically decreasing in OA training iterations n. SETUP: X|C+,n ~ N(mu_S, sigma^2); X|C-,n ~ N(mu_N(n), sigma^2); d_prime(n) = [mu_S - mu_N(n)] / sigma. PREMISES (SDT-native, not K1-K7): P1=baseline discrimination d_prime(0) > 0; P2=OA training weakly increases mu_N(n); P3=strict increase while gradient nonzero (mu_N(n+1) > mu_N(n) for n < N*); P4=mu_S stable (not improving from OA training); P5=CPP-anchored ceiling mu_N(n) < mu_S for finite n. PROOF: P3 gives mu_N(n+1) > mu_N(n) => mu_S - mu_N(n+1) < mu_S - mu_N(n) => d_prime(n+1) < d_prime(n). ASYMPTOTE: d_prime(inf) = mu_S(1 - ceiling_AATE)/sigma > 0 for CPP > 0; d_prime -> 0 only as ceiling_AATE -> 1 (zero CPP). A_prime(n) also strictly decreasing (monotone function of d_prime). INDEPENDENCE: derivation uses only SDT + empirical premise (OA training improves compliance appearance); does NOT use CIA, TCA, AIIP, K1, K2, K3-K7. Parallel derivation to AATE-SMD (which uses CIA+TCA). QUANTITATIVE PREDICTIONS: (Q1) A_prime(M_n) < A_prime(M_{n-1}) for successive RLHF checkpoints; (Q2) cross-temporal calibration failure: false positive rate increases at generation n+1 under criterion calibrated at n; (Q3) d_prime threshold effects (d_prime < 1.0 = marginal, < 0.5 = useless); (Q4) CPP moderation of d_prime(inf); (Q5) criterion shift: optimal beta*(n) shifts, fixed-beta instruments degrade in accuracy. EP6 CANDIDATE: A_prime-deterioration test across RLHF checkpoints using K5 Test 3 as CA instrument; requires training checkpoint access. Document: state/decisions/aate-sdt-theorem.md.","category":"epistemology","confidence":0.78,"created":"2026-04-29T14:44:13+00:00"}
